The little nursing
babies who were--

00:14:45.890 --> 00:14:48.680 align:middle line:10%
they had real sharp knives--

00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:52.550 align:middle line:10%
and who would play with
a sharp knife right

00:14:52.550 --> 00:14:55.280 align:middle line:10%
when they were at
their mother's breast.

00:14:55.280 --> 00:15:04.010 align:middle line:10%
And Jean shouted out again, oh,
that child will hurt his mother

00:15:04.010 --> 00:15:05.690 align:middle line:10%
with that knife.

00:15:05.690 --> 00:15:09.830 align:middle line:10%
And the question she got
back was, but why would

00:15:09.830 --> 00:15:12.530 align:middle line:10%
a child want to
hurt his own mother?

00:15:12.530 --> 00:15:14.870 align:middle line:10%
With that kind of an
answer right and left,

00:15:14.870 --> 00:15:20.510 align:middle line:10%
she discovered that a child
born into that world--

00:15:20.510 --> 00:15:27.390 align:middle line:10%
if nurtured and not
interfered with--

00:15:27.390 --> 00:15:33.405 align:middle line:10%
had this remarkable intelligence
for responding exactly the way

00:15:33.405 --> 00:15:37.480 align:middle line:10%
they needed to get along in
the world very beautifully,

00:15:37.480 --> 00:15:45.010 align:middle line:10%
and that we lose that through
teaching children to behave.

00:15:45.010 --> 00:15:49.230 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHS] and beyond that,
I could go on and on.

00:15:49.230 --> 00:15:50.970 align:middle line:90%
But Jean Liedloff is--

00:15:50.970 --> 00:15:52.620 align:middle line:90%
along with Robert Wolff--

00:15:52.620 --> 00:15:58.290 align:middle line:84%
two people I would
suggest to anyone to read.

00:15:58.290 --> 00:16:02.240 align:middle line:84%
Robert Wolff wrote a
book, Original Wisdom.

00:16:02.240 --> 00:16:04.850 align:middle line:90%


00:16:04.850 --> 00:16:07.910 align:middle line:10%
If anyone would read that
and catch on to what Wolff

00:16:07.910 --> 00:16:10.920 align:middle line:10%
is saying, it would change--

00:16:10.920 --> 00:16:12.960 align:middle line:10%
and would accept it--

00:16:12.960 --> 00:16:16.050 align:middle line:10%
it would just change everything.

00:16:16.050 --> 00:16:22.125 align:middle line:84%
He was a Dutchman, sent
by the Dutch government

00:16:22.125 --> 00:16:26.830 align:middle line:90%
to the Malaysian people.

00:16:26.830 --> 00:16:34.020 align:middle line:84%
And while there, he found
these remarkable people

00:16:34.020 --> 00:16:35.420 align:middle line:90%
called the Senoi--

00:16:35.420 --> 00:16:40.470 align:middle line:84%
S-E-G-N-O-I-A,
something like that.

00:16:40.470 --> 00:16:45.340 align:middle line:10%
When he was with the Senoi,
which took him a long time

00:16:45.340 --> 00:16:50.090 align:middle line:10%
to win a place with them and
for them to recognize him--

00:16:50.090 --> 00:16:54.220 align:middle line:10%
when he was with this group
of forest people, the forest

00:16:54.220 --> 00:17:00.730 align:middle line:10%
itself was quite different when
they were with him and showing

00:17:00.730 --> 00:17:04.190 align:middle line:10%
him than without them.

00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:09.220 align:middle line:10%
In other words, they
influenced their environment

00:17:09.220 --> 00:17:14.790 align:middle line:10%
and lived in their environment
that they were creating.

00:17:14.790 --> 00:17:27.020 align:middle line:84%
He experienced true divinity,
true heaven kind of a thing.

00:17:27.020 --> 00:17:31.880 align:middle line:10%
And when a friend of
mine, Thom Hartmann

00:17:31.880 --> 00:17:35.360 align:middle line:10%
found Wolff still alive
way up in his 90's he

00:17:35.360 --> 00:17:40.940 align:middle line:10%
had retired to Hawaii
because the climate was

00:17:40.940 --> 00:17:44.270 align:middle line:10%
most in keeping with his needs.

00:17:44.270 --> 00:17:47.370 align:middle line:90%


00:17:47.370 --> 00:17:51.860 align:middle line:10%
All Wolff could say
when Hartmann asked him

00:17:51.860 --> 00:17:55.940 align:middle line:10%
about his experience--

00:17:55.940 --> 00:17:58.820 align:middle line:10%
he had written a
diary, by the way,

00:17:58.820 --> 00:18:03.080 align:middle line:10%
and Hartmann found the diary,
and he had gone and sought

00:18:03.080 --> 00:18:09.080 align:middle line:10%
out where Wolff was, even
now, way up in his 90s,

00:18:09.080 --> 00:18:13.240 align:middle line:10%
and was interviewing--
that's how this came about.

00:18:13.240 --> 00:18:23.900 align:middle line:84%
And all Wolff could say, we
have no idea what we have lost.

00:18:23.900 --> 00:18:26.500 align:middle line:90%


00:18:26.500 --> 00:18:33.470 align:middle line:10%
And I think that that's the
thing that just kind of blows

00:18:33.470 --> 00:18:35.900 align:middle line:10%
me out of orbit occasionally.

00:18:35.900 --> 00:18:38.770 align:middle line:10%
We have no idea of
what we've lost.

00:18:38.770 --> 00:18:42.130 align:middle line:10%
Just as we're talking about
there are new sciences and all

00:18:42.130 --> 00:18:45.780 align:middle line:10%
the things they can do, and we
can blow up the whole world.

00:18:45.780 --> 00:18:49.760 align:middle line:84%
And we can trace the universe
and all this nonsense.

00:18:49.760 --> 00:18:53.390 align:middle line:90%
And the people suffer.

00:18:53.390 --> 00:18:56.240 align:middle line:10%
>> When Robert Wolff said, we
have no idea what we have lost,

00:18:56.240 --> 00:18:57.170 align:middle line:10%
he was--

00:18:57.170 --> 00:19:00.420 align:middle line:10%
he was talking about the essence
of what it is to be human,

00:19:00.420 --> 00:19:03.590 align:middle line:10%
the original title of his book.

00:19:03.590 --> 00:19:07.640 align:middle line:84%
What it is to love each
other, to care for each other,

00:19:07.640 --> 00:19:11.870 align:middle line:84%
to be part of nature, to be
interpenetrated by nature,

00:19:11.870 --> 00:19:15.950 align:middle line:90%
to realize that we're--

00:19:15.950 --> 00:19:18.050 align:middle line:84%
it's a terrible cliche,
but that we're all one--

00:19:18.050 --> 00:19:20.090 align:middle line:84%
and not just all
of us, everything--

00:19:20.090 --> 00:19:24.470 align:middle line:84%
that it's all one
thing, and that there

00:19:24.470 --> 00:19:27.050 align:middle line:84%
is a depth and a
beauty to all of this,

00:19:27.050 --> 00:19:29.300 align:middle line:84%
and that one of the most
powerful forces in the world

00:19:29.300 --> 00:19:30.470 align:middle line:90%
is love.

00:19:30.470 --> 00:19:35.330 align:middle line:84%
And you know, love and
light, and not in some kind

00:19:35.330 --> 00:19:37.100 align:middle line:90%
of new age, cliched way.

00:19:37.100 --> 00:19:39.830 align:middle line:84%
This was just
fundamental right down--

00:19:39.830 --> 00:19:42.410 align:middle line:84%
you know, met these people,
lived with these people,

00:19:42.410 --> 00:19:44.360 align:middle line:84%
knew these people,
learned their language,

00:19:44.360 --> 00:19:48.500 align:middle line:84%
slept in their villages,
dreamed their dreams,

00:19:48.500 --> 00:19:50.990 align:middle line:84%
and changed my life
as a result of it.

00:19:50.990 --> 00:19:54.200 align:middle line:84%
That was Robert Wolff's
story, essentially,

00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:56.520 align:middle line:84%
and it was such a
meaningful story.

00:19:56.520 --> 00:19:58.440 align:middle line:84%
And like I said, it
touched me deeply,

00:19:58.440 --> 00:20:02.810 align:middle line:84%
and I know it touched
Joe deeply as well.

00:20:02.810 --> 00:20:08.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Joe and I met in the
early summer of 1969.

00:20:08.450 --> 00:20:11.120 align:middle line:84%
I had just graduated
from college,

00:20:11.120 --> 00:20:14.720 align:middle line:84%
and I was interviewing for
my first job as a teacher--

00:20:14.720 --> 00:20:17.930 align:middle line:84%
music teacher-- in
Western Massachusetts.

00:20:17.930 --> 00:20:21.950 align:middle line:84%
And Joe was also a music
teacher at the time.

00:20:21.950 --> 00:20:24.500 align:middle line:10%
When he wrote Crack
in the Cosmic Egg,

00:20:24.500 --> 00:20:26.330 align:middle line:10%
that's when I first knew him--

00:20:26.330 --> 00:20:27.260 align:middle line:10%
his first book.

00:20:27.260 --> 00:20:31.010 align:middle line:10%
And he was still teaching
school at the time.

00:20:31.010 --> 00:20:33.830 align:middle line:84%
He taught maybe two or
three years after that,

00:20:33.830 --> 00:20:36.740 align:middle line:84%
and then there came
a point that he just

00:20:36.740 --> 00:20:41.240 align:middle line:84%
wanted to follow his
path, or his dharma,

00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:45.110 align:middle line:84%
and write about
what he felt inside.

00:20:45.110 --> 00:20:50.940 align:middle line:84%
And all the ideas he had,
he wanted to express them.

00:20:50.940 --> 00:20:53.210 align:middle line:84%
And so at that point, he
said he was never going

00:20:53.210 --> 00:20:55.970 align:middle line:90%
to work for anybody again.

00:20:55.970 --> 00:20:58.160 align:middle line:84%
He was going to
do his own thing.

00:20:58.160 --> 00:21:03.980 align:middle line:84%
He was probably in his mid 40s
by then, maybe mid to late 40s.

00:21:03.980 --> 00:21:07.160 align:middle line:84%
And yes, things
changed at that point.

00:21:07.160 --> 00:21:10.220 align:middle line:84%
And he started, especially
when Magical Child came out,

00:21:10.220 --> 00:21:12.530 align:middle line:84%
he really started
lecturing a lot.

00:21:12.530 --> 00:21:14.960 align:middle line:84%
He had a lecture
person that arranged

00:21:14.960 --> 00:21:17.860 align:middle line:90%
lectures all over the country.

00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:19.830 align:middle line:84%
And that's what he
did from then on.

00:21:19.830 --> 00:21:23.530 align:middle line:84%
He wrote, and he lectured
for the rest of his life.

00:21:23.530 --> 00:21:24.580 align:middle line:90%
That was his only focus.

00:21:24.580 --> 00:21:28.270 align:middle line:84%
He didn't care about how people
saw him or thought about him.

00:21:28.270 --> 00:21:33.000 align:middle line:84%
He just wanted to get his
ideas across to his audience.

00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:36.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Joe liked to be
kind of anonymous.

00:21:36.480 --> 00:21:40.710 align:middle line:10%
He liked to-- he liked for
people to pay attention

00:21:40.710 --> 00:21:42.150 align:middle line:10%
to what it was he was saying.

00:21:42.150 --> 00:21:44.640 align:middle line:84%
He didn't like for
people to pay attention

00:21:44.640 --> 00:21:46.650 align:middle line:90%
to who he was as a person.

00:21:46.650 --> 00:21:48.630 align:middle line:84%
And that was a very
important thing for him--

00:21:48.630 --> 00:21:52.950 align:middle line:84%
that he wasn't out there to
present an ego personality

00:21:52.950 --> 00:21:54.330 align:middle line:90%
for people to remember.

00:21:54.330 --> 00:21:56.460 align:middle line:84%
He was out there to say
things that he really

00:21:56.460 --> 00:21:58.560 align:middle line:90%
felt were true and important.

00:21:58.560 --> 00:22:01.680 align:middle line:84%
And so I know that
it's those things

00:22:01.680 --> 00:22:04.860 align:middle line:84%
that he said that he
wants people to remember.

00:22:04.860 --> 00:22:08.318 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:22:08.318 --> 00:22:18.700 align:middle line:90%


00:22:18.700 --> 00:22:24.460 align:middle line:84%
>> We dramatically influence
the kind of experience

00:22:24.460 --> 00:22:25.810 align:middle line:90%
we're having.

00:22:25.810 --> 00:22:28.760 align:middle line:84%
Everyone thinks that all
of this is happening to me,

00:22:28.760 --> 00:22:30.680 align:middle line:90%
and that's not the case.

00:22:30.680 --> 00:22:36.470 align:middle line:84%
It's what we are doing, and
it's reflected back to us.

00:22:36.470 --> 00:22:41.980 align:middle line:10%
We're each responsible
for what kind of forest

00:22:41.980 --> 00:22:46.720 align:middle line:10%
we're going through, whether
it's a beautiful place

00:22:46.720 --> 00:22:49.930 align:middle line:10%
or whether it's a nightmare.

00:22:49.930 --> 00:22:54.070 align:middle line:84%
The majority of us are
in constant conflict

00:22:54.070 --> 00:22:58.520 align:middle line:90%
with ourselves over survival.

00:22:58.520 --> 00:23:02.160 align:middle line:84%
Survival takes--
that's number one.

00:23:02.160 --> 00:23:05.840 align:middle line:84%
And we have other
things we want to do,

00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:10.130 align:middle line:84%
but if it's against the
survival impulse in us,

00:23:10.130 --> 00:23:11.600 align:middle line:90%
we go for the survival.

00:23:11.600 --> 00:23:14.900 align:middle line:90%
There's no doubt of that.

00:23:14.900 --> 00:23:22.940 align:middle line:84%
And what I had discovered-- and
it really, really was true--

00:23:22.940 --> 00:23:26.690 align:middle line:84%
I discovered that I
couldn't be burned,

00:23:26.690 --> 00:23:29.270 align:middle line:90%
at least not by cigarettes.

00:23:29.270 --> 00:23:35.950 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was in my first and
only year, semester in college.

00:23:35.950 --> 00:23:39.950 align:middle line:84%
And this was in the college
dormitory, and a bunch of us

00:23:39.950 --> 00:23:43.180 align:middle line:84%
and I discovered that
I couldn't be burned.

00:23:43.180 --> 00:23:46.410 align:middle line:84%
And I used up a whole
package of Pall Malls,

00:23:46.410 --> 00:23:51.010 align:middle line:84%
those great, big, huge, fat,
thick, heavy cigarettes--

00:23:51.010 --> 00:23:54.410 align:middle line:84%
whole batch of them, getting
them going full blast

00:23:54.410 --> 00:23:58.370 align:middle line:84%
and showing the
boys at the table

00:23:58.370 --> 00:23:59.870 align:middle line:84%
that I couldn't be
burned with them.

00:23:59.870 --> 00:24:02.960 align:middle line:84%
I was finally putting
them out on my eyelid.

00:24:02.960 --> 00:24:06.770 align:middle line:84%
I tried to keep my eye open,
but I couldn't-- reflex was too

00:24:06.770 --> 00:24:09.740 align:middle line:90%
strong to protect my eye.

00:24:09.740 --> 00:24:11.060 align:middle line:10%
And my lips--

00:24:11.060 --> 00:24:16.810 align:middle line:10%
I finally had gotten three
or four I'm going at once

00:24:16.810 --> 00:24:22.070 align:middle line:10%
and reversed them and put the
hot end in between my lips

00:24:22.070 --> 00:24:25.370 align:middle line:10%
and blew sparks
all over everybody.

00:24:25.370 --> 00:24:26.930 align:middle line:10%
I was having a ball.

00:24:26.930 --> 00:24:30.530 align:middle line:10%
My roommate was terribly
upset because he said,

00:24:30.530 --> 00:24:32.750 align:middle line:10%
you'll be sorry tomorrow.

00:24:32.750 --> 00:24:34.480 align:middle line:10%
And I'll never forget
the next morning,

00:24:34.480 --> 00:24:39.980 align:middle line:10%
he couldn't wait to look at me
to see how badly burned I was--

00:24:39.980 --> 00:24:42.050 align:middle line:10%
no trace at all.

00:24:42.050 --> 00:24:43.190 align:middle line:10%
And I told him--

00:24:43.190 --> 00:24:47.150 align:middle line:10%
I said, but I knew
there could not be.

00:24:47.150 --> 00:24:52.670 align:middle line:84%
And out of that, I
really developed this

00:24:52.670 --> 00:24:55.910 align:middle line:90%
to a pretty good extent--

00:24:55.910 --> 00:24:57.890 align:middle line:90%
unconflicted behavior.

00:24:57.890 --> 00:25:00.830 align:middle line:10%
So long as my system
has no conflict--

00:25:00.830 --> 00:25:05.000 align:middle line:10%
one part of me saying do, the
other part say don't, and all

00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:06.990 align:middle line:10%
of us know that--

00:25:06.990 --> 00:25:11.320 align:middle line:10%
oh, should I buy that, well,
we wrestled back and forth

00:25:11.320 --> 00:25:13.220 align:middle line:10%
between whether
we should or not.

00:25:13.220 --> 00:25:19.470 align:middle line:84%
Or should we attempt
this venture or not?

00:25:19.470 --> 00:25:22.880 align:middle line:90%
We debate these back and forth.

00:25:22.880 --> 00:25:27.070 align:middle line:10%
And unconflicted behaviors--
when all conflict is gone--

00:25:27.070 --> 00:25:32.990 align:middle line:10%
and at that point, you can do
anything you take a notion.

00:25:32.990 --> 00:25:35.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I
went up to the cliff

00:25:35.060 --> 00:25:37.400 align:middle line:90%
at Palos Verdes in California.

00:25:37.400 --> 00:25:41.920 align:middle line:90%


00:25:41.920 --> 00:25:45.530 align:middle line:10%
It's the highest cliff on
that coastline, I guess.

00:25:45.530 --> 00:25:49.700 align:middle line:10%
And I went up, and it started
just collapsing underneath me

00:25:49.700 --> 00:25:52.700 align:middle line:10%
and dumped me right
back down on the ground.

00:25:52.700 --> 00:25:54.500 align:middle line:90%
It was a rotten cliff.

00:25:54.500 --> 00:25:57.380 align:middle line:84%
There wasn't a stable
rock in the whole place.

00:25:57.380 --> 00:26:00.610 align:middle line:84%
And that's when all
of a sudden, this

00:26:00.610 --> 00:26:04.070 align:middle line:84%
unconflicted behavior,
which I'd been playing

00:26:04.070 --> 00:26:06.890 align:middle line:84%
with for a long time,
I just turned it over

00:26:06.890 --> 00:26:11.840 align:middle line:84%
to that unconflicted behavior,
and I went up that cliff.

00:26:11.840 --> 00:26:17.860 align:middle line:84%
And the thing collapsed under
me every step of the way I took.

00:26:17.860 --> 00:26:19.790 align:middle line:84%
And when I finally
came to the place

00:26:19.790 --> 00:26:22.790 align:middle line:84%
where there was the
overhang, that overhang

00:26:22.790 --> 00:26:26.420 align:middle line:90%
was at least 20 feet in all.

00:26:26.420 --> 00:26:30.890 align:middle line:10%
There was hanging just by
the roots, and I went up,

00:26:30.890 --> 00:26:36.648 align:middle line:10%
and I suddenly knew only because
I was reaching for something.

00:26:36.648 --> 00:26:38.440 align:middle line:10%
There was nothing there,
and I looked down.

00:26:38.440 --> 00:26:40.100 align:middle line:10%
There was nothing below me.

00:26:40.100 --> 00:26:42.470 align:middle line:10%
I was on that overhang.

00:26:42.470 --> 00:26:46.970 align:middle line:10%
And this tremendous
elation began to fill me,

00:26:46.970 --> 00:26:50.510 align:middle line:10%
and I went the whole
distance unable to see

00:26:50.510 --> 00:26:53.600 align:middle line:10%
where I was going, just
feeling with my hands

00:26:53.600 --> 00:26:58.250 align:middle line:10%
and moving accordingly.

00:26:58.250 --> 00:27:03.470 align:middle line:10%
And I moved that whole
distance of about 20 feet

00:27:03.470 --> 00:27:08.540 align:middle line:10%
in thin air, touching rocks and
stuff that immediately fell out

00:27:08.540 --> 00:27:09.840 align:middle line:10%
from under me.

00:27:09.840 --> 00:27:15.440 align:middle line:84%
But I knew inside me, I
could not possibly be hurt.

00:27:15.440 --> 00:27:19.190 align:middle line:84%
And people say, well, those are
things you're adding afterward.

00:27:19.190 --> 00:27:20.290 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:27:20.290 --> 00:27:24.420 align:middle line:84%
They're the reason I got
out of that not only alive,

00:27:24.420 --> 00:27:25.860 align:middle line:90%
but elated.

00:27:25.860 --> 00:27:29.130 align:middle line:84%
And when I finally
got to the top,

00:27:29.130 --> 00:27:32.700 align:middle line:84%
the group I had been
having a picnic with

00:27:32.700 --> 00:27:36.210 align:middle line:84%
had moved over to
that very area.

00:27:36.210 --> 00:27:43.530 align:middle line:84%
And I popped up over the edge,
and it was an impossible thing.

00:27:43.530 --> 00:27:48.000 align:middle line:10%
I couldn't just materialize
out of thin air like that.

00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:53.490 align:middle line:84%
But the elation in me, this
huge exhilaration filled me.

00:27:53.490 --> 00:27:57.030 align:middle line:10%
And I started pounding
my chest and screaming.

00:27:57.030 --> 00:28:01.500 align:middle line:10%
They said I screamed with this--

00:28:01.500 --> 00:28:04.080 align:middle line:10%
they thought I
had gone delirious

00:28:04.080 --> 00:28:08.440 align:middle line:10%
with the ecstasy which
I felt over that.

00:28:08.440 --> 00:28:13.620 align:middle line:84%
And what I felt is that I
had taken death into myself

00:28:13.620 --> 00:28:15.550 align:middle line:90%
and had conquered it.

00:28:15.550 --> 00:28:21.630 align:middle line:84%
Talk about romantic, adolescent
stuff, but I had taken death,

00:28:21.630 --> 00:28:25.830 align:middle line:84%
I had accepted it, and
I had conquered it,

00:28:25.830 --> 00:28:27.150 align:middle line:90%
and it would change everything.

00:28:27.150 --> 00:28:28.920 align:middle line:90%
From that point on, I would--

00:28:28.920 --> 00:28:31.580 align:middle line:84%
nothing could ever
be the same again.

00:28:31.580 --> 00:28:35.572 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:28:35.572 --> 00:28:47.060 align:middle line:90%


00:28:47.060 --> 00:28:49.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Joe has always been
a very spiritual person.

00:28:49.730 --> 00:28:53.190 align:middle line:10%
He's always had tremendous
inner experiences.

00:28:53.190 --> 00:28:57.320 align:middle line:10%
We were in Siddah Yoga a little
over 10 years, went to India

00:28:57.320 --> 00:29:03.080 align:middle line:10%
many times in the winter, spent
a lot of time at the Ashram

00:29:03.080 --> 00:29:05.628 align:middle line:10%
in New York in the summers.

00:29:05.628 --> 00:29:07.670 align:middle line:84%
That was a big part of
our lives for a long time.

00:29:07.670 --> 00:29:10.580 align:middle line:84%
Joe did many, many
talks for them.

00:29:10.580 --> 00:29:12.740 align:middle line:84%
He did a lot of--
the call it seva,

00:29:12.740 --> 00:29:17.710 align:middle line:90%
where you do work for the yoga.

00:29:17.710 --> 00:29:21.590 align:middle line:84%
And he did many
talks, and he was--

00:29:21.590 --> 00:29:25.140 align:middle line:90%


00:29:25.140 --> 00:29:26.541 align:middle line:90%
people loved him there.

00:29:26.541 --> 00:29:29.307 align:middle line:90%
