00:29:29.307 --> 00:29:30.690 align:middle line:90%


00:29:30.690 --> 00:29:35.760 align:middle line:10%
>> One of the first things I
ever found when I went to visit

00:29:35.760 --> 00:29:41.960 align:middle line:10%
this meditation master in India
by the name of Muktananda --

00:29:41.960 --> 00:29:44.730 align:middle line:10%
he was very famous,
and rightly so

00:29:44.730 --> 00:29:48.300 align:middle line:10%
because he is a
very remarkable man.

00:29:48.300 --> 00:29:51.030 align:middle line:10%
But one of the things he--

00:29:51.030 --> 00:29:55.440 align:middle line:10%
the first thing, I think,
he said to me was--

00:29:55.440 --> 00:29:57.660 align:middle line:10%
he had to speak
to an interpreter

00:29:57.660 --> 00:30:01.460 align:middle line:10%
because he didn't speak English.

00:30:01.460 --> 00:30:04.950 align:middle line:10%
He said, the heart--

00:30:04.950 --> 00:30:06.590 align:middle line:10%
and right out of
the clear blue sky,

00:30:06.590 --> 00:30:10.140 align:middle line:10%
he didn't know anything
about me except for I

00:30:10.140 --> 00:30:11.840 align:middle line:10%
came with my family there--

00:30:11.840 --> 00:30:19.730 align:middle line:10%
is that the heart is the
source of everything,

00:30:19.730 --> 00:30:23.390 align:middle line:10%
and there is only one heart.

00:30:23.390 --> 00:30:25.990 align:middle line:10%
He said the heart
beating in my chest

00:30:25.990 --> 00:30:29.360 align:middle line:10%
is the same as the one
beating in your chest

00:30:29.360 --> 00:30:31.400 align:middle line:10%
and everyone's chest.

00:30:31.400 --> 00:30:34.400 align:middle line:90%
And the heart is God.

00:30:34.400 --> 00:30:36.740 align:middle line:10%
The heart is the creator.

00:30:36.740 --> 00:30:39.770 align:middle line:84%
The heart is the
source of everything,

00:30:39.770 --> 00:30:43.280 align:middle line:90%
and there's only one of those.

00:30:43.280 --> 00:30:51.950 align:middle line:10%
And once one understands that
there is only one heart, that

00:30:51.950 --> 00:30:57.600 align:middle line:10%
is repeated in every
single human, the same one,

00:30:57.600 --> 00:31:00.920 align:middle line:10%
but always purely
individual, how

00:31:00.920 --> 00:31:05.390 align:middle line:10%
can we be purely individual
and universal at the same time?

00:31:05.390 --> 00:31:07.670 align:middle line:10%
That's the great mystery.

00:31:07.670 --> 00:31:09.470 align:middle line:10%
It really is.

00:31:09.470 --> 00:31:12.860 align:middle line:10%
But understanding that,
then you never again

00:31:12.860 --> 00:31:19.210 align:middle line:10%
have to question what
you feel in your heart.

00:31:19.210 --> 00:31:21.270 align:middle line:10%
>> Joe's great--

00:31:21.270 --> 00:31:26.050 align:middle line:10%
I think Joe's great
legacy was that you

00:31:26.050 --> 00:31:29.710 align:middle line:10%
can compare brilliant
mind with brilliant heart,

00:31:29.710 --> 00:31:32.680 align:middle line:10%
that it's all a piece
of the same light.

00:31:32.680 --> 00:31:37.660 align:middle line:84%
His work academically was
as good as he could make it.

00:31:37.660 --> 00:31:45.070 align:middle line:84%
He brought people in, scholars
that I had never heard of,

00:31:45.070 --> 00:31:46.960 align:middle line:84%
many who had simply
been cast aside

00:31:46.960 --> 00:31:48.940 align:middle line:84%
because the larger
culture doesn't

00:31:48.940 --> 00:31:51.190 align:middle line:90%
know how to assimilate them.

00:31:51.190 --> 00:31:52.490 align:middle line:90%
And I read them.

00:31:52.490 --> 00:31:54.460 align:middle line:90%
And I heard Joe talk about them.

00:31:54.460 --> 00:31:57.340 align:middle line:84%
And I read their books
in manuscript form.

00:31:57.340 --> 00:32:00.640 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that they were
coming from the same place

00:32:00.640 --> 00:32:05.200 align:middle line:84%
that Joe was, and it was
this kind of we can balance--

00:32:05.200 --> 00:32:08.900 align:middle line:84%
we can balance our
thoughtfulness with our caring,

00:32:08.900 --> 00:32:11.590 align:middle line:84%
and that we don't have
to sacrifice either one.

00:32:11.590 --> 00:32:14.440 align:middle line:84%
We don't rush in and
emotionally throw ourselves

00:32:14.440 --> 00:32:21.250 align:middle line:84%
into the middle of nothing,
that we can bring spirit

00:32:21.250 --> 00:32:27.230 align:middle line:90%
and word and gesture together.

00:32:27.230 --> 00:32:31.280 align:middle line:84%
It just takes a lot of
focus and a lot of heart

00:32:31.280 --> 00:32:35.616 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of caring
and a big vision.

00:32:35.616 --> 00:32:38.484 align:middle line:90%
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

